INSTALL THE REQUIRED SOFTWARE
1.) Python Mutagen (for mp3 header parsing) (http://code.google.com/p/mutagen/)
2.) Lame MP3 Encoder (http://lame.sourceforge.net/)
3.) Python 2.5 or 2.6 (http://www.python.org)

RUN THE SOFTWARE

1.) Change the examples/default.cfg file to your liking.
2.) Create a new examples/file.list file with the MP3 files you want to play 
    (I like to just do 'find /abs/path/to/dir -name *.mp3 > examples/file.list')
3.) chmod 755 ocradio/ocradio.py
4.) Run ocradio (like 'ocradio/ocradio.py -c examples/default.cfg').
5.) To exist just Ctrl-C (I know it's lame!)